    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Service Manual - Manifolds and Exhaust Gas Recirculation (EGR) - Installation - Exhaust Gas
        Recirculation (EGR) Valve
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Exhaust Gas Recirculation (EGR) Valve</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate new O-rings with a solution of dish washing soap and water (approximate 50/50
                mix).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the gasket onto the EGR valve first.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the two smaller O-rings seals onto the EGR valve.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, make certain that the EGR valve is completely seated within the intake
                    manifold prior to inserting bolts.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f3000428" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ17/J17004.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Seat EGR valve by hand</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">When installing the EGR valve into the intake manifold, make sure it is completely seated by
                hand before installing bolts.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Thread two bolts (M6 x 35) by hand and tighten, alternating between both bolts to the
                <hotlnk document="eges3001_73.xml" xrefid="E30004B">Special Torque</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Reconnect electrical harness to EGR valve.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove tools, parts and equipment.</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Reinstall all safety guards, shields and covers after servicing the engine.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Make sure all tools, magnetic covers, loose parts and service equipment are removed from
                    the engine area after all work is done.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
